        <div class="faq-right">
            <div class="faq-accordion">
                <button class="faq-acc-item">
                    <span class="faq-acc-q">What is IRMAA?</span>
                    <span class="faq-acc-icon">+</span>
                    <div class="faq-acc-a">IRMAA (Income-Related Monthly Adjustment Amount) is a surcharge added to Medicare Part B and Part D premiums for higher-income beneficiaries. The surcharge is based on your Modified Adjusted Gross Income from two years prior and can add over $1,000/month per person to your Medicare costs.</div>
                </button>
                <button class="faq-acc-item">
                    <span class="faq-acc-q">What are the 2025 IRMAA thresholds?</span>
                    <span class="faq-acc-icon">+</span>
                    <div class="faq-acc-a">For 2025, single filers with income over $103,000 (married filing jointly over $206,000) will pay IRMAA surcharges. The surcharges increase at multiple income tiers, with the highest tier kicking in at $500,000 for singles and $750,000 for married couples. We help you stay below the first threshold to avoid thousands in extra premiums.</div>
                </button>
                <button class="faq-acc-item">
                    <span class="faq-acc-q">Can I avoid IRMAA if I'm already paying it?</span>
                    <span class="faq-acc-icon">+</span>
                    <div class="faq-acc-a">Yes, with forward planning. IRMAA is based on income from two years ago, so we manage your income today to avoid surcharges two years from now. We also review potential life-changing event appeals if your income has decreased due to retirement, death of a spouse, or other qualifying events.</div>
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
